# STRATEGICLAND — Performance System

> Performance is **the medium**.
> Cinema requires **time**, and time requires **frame budget**.
> Spectacle is **never** an excuse for jank. Spectacle that drops frames is broken spectacle.

---

## 1. Performance Philosophy

- The site must run at **60 FPS sustained** on a 2019 MacBook Pro and 2021 mid-range Android.
- The site must achieve **LCP ≤ 2.0s** on 4G mobile, **CLS = 0**, **INP ≤ 200ms**.
- Every byte added must be defended. Every effect added must be measured.
- A scene that drops frames is a **failed scene** — even if it looks beautiful in screenshots.

---

## 2. Performance Budgets (LOCKED)

### 2.1 Asset budgets
| Asset                       | Budget                        |
|-----------------------------|-------------------------------|
| First-load JS (gzip)        | ≤ 180 KB                       |
| First-load CSS (gzip)       | ≤ 30 KB                        |
| Initial fonts (woff2)       | ≤ 90 KB total (2 weights)      |
| Hero image (above fold)     | ≤ 220 KB (AVIF) / ≤ 350 KB (WebP) |
| Per-chapter additional JS   | ≤ 60 KB gzip                   |
| Per-chapter shaders + textures | ≤ 80 KB                     |
| Total page weight (no cache, home) | ≤ 1.4 MB                |

### 2.2 Runtime budgets (per frame, 16.6ms)
| Subsystem                | Budget |
|--------------------------|--------|
| Layout / paint            | ≤ 4ms  |
| GSAP timelines + ticker   | ≤ 3ms  |
| WebGL render              | ≤ 4ms  |
| Lenis update              | ≤ 1ms  |
| React reconciliation      | ≤ 2ms  |
| Headroom                  | ≥ 2.6ms|

### 2.3 Counts
| Element                          | Cap |
|----------------------------------|-----|
| Concurrent GSAP tweens           | ≤ 16 |
| Concurrent ScrollTriggers        | ≤ 24 |
| Active particles (WebGL)         | ≤ 1500 |
| Total scene tris (active chapter)| ≤ 20k |
| `will-change` elements at any time | ≤ 8 |

